The Ministry of Foreign Affairs has told off two former America diplomats to Kenya calling for President Donald Trump’s intervention in the country’s post election political stalemate. Foreign Affairs Principal Secretary ,Ambassador Macharia Kamau responding to an article written by former Ambassadors William Bellamy and Johnie Carson termed it as missiniformed, blatant lies and full of half truths. Macharia’s condemnation comes ahead of a crucial maiden visit by US Secretary of state Rex Tillerson on Friday this week. 